          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A and R both are wrong</span></span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Assertion (A): After overnight fasting, levels of glucose transporters are reduced in adipocytes. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Reasoning (R): Adipocytes are insulin-sensitive tissues and as an early response to the hormone, the glucose transporters are externalized. </span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q1512355",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 29811,
